column5: Still out and about, still chasin da trout. Fun fight. O4T
Big mouth on that one.  Must make whitefish nervous.   	great pic.
Thanks folks - this one made my day... thinking it is dining on cisco.
Nice fish, buddy! Looking a bit grey on top, and what's that, a BEARD!!!!! 😁 Doug
Doug... we will get out for another ice fishing adventure... before we no longer recognize each other. 😄
and no DEATH MARCHES on Charleston, either!!!  I should replay that one, it was a classic......... Doug
O4T with his long legs, and a young lad who is about 6 foot 13...  classic reporting!
What the heck, let's run it again for the memories
I start nailing them in May on Lake Ontario 9-16lb range from 100' of water.  Need to burb air bubbles out before releasing else they have difficulty diving back. Lake Trout Beautiful fish.
